message.content:
I need to design an implementation plan for restyling profile widgets in a React app. Here's the full context:

## Reference Design
The user provided a reference image of a card/profile bio style with these characteristics:
- **Card Background:** Warm cream/off-white (like #f8f5ef or similar warm beige)
- **Card Shape:** Rounded corners (~16-20px), subtle soft shadow
- **Font:** Handwritten/casual style font - looks like "Patrick Hand", "Caveat", or "Comic Neue" - a clean but hand-drawn aesthetic
- **Content Layout:** Vertical flow with images at top, highlighted banner/pill sections in green/teal, bullet-point lists with emojis, links at bottom
- **Color Accent:** Green/teal highlight banner for important sections
- **Overall Feel:** Warm, hand-crafted, personal, sketch-like

## Current Architecture

### CSS Files to Modify:
1. **`client/src/components/ProfilePage/myprofile.css`** - Owner's profile widget styles
2. **`client/src/components/VisitProfile/visitProfile.css`** - Visitor's profile widget styles
3. **`client/src/index.css`** - Global CSS variables and font imports

### Current Widget Card Styles (MyProfile):
```css
.profile-widget-card {
  position: absolute;
  width: fit-content;
  max-width: min(100%, 520px);
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  background-color: var(--bg-glass);
  backdrop-filter: blur(25px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(25px);
  padding: 0.5rem 0.7rem;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  transition: box-shadow 0.12s ease;
}
```

Widget typography:
```css
.profile-widget-title {
  margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;
  font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  font-weight: 650;
}
.profile-widget-note {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  line-height: 1.45;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
  word-break: break-word;
}
```

Block typography:
```css
.profile-widget-block-text {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  line-height: 1.4;
}
.profile-widget-block-title {
  margin: 0 0 0.2rem 0;
  font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 650;
}
.profile-widget-block-note {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.76rem;
  line-height: 1.35;
}
```

### Current Visited Widget Card Styles:
```css
.visited-profile-widget-card {
  position: absolute;
  width: fit-content;
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  background-color: var(--bg-glass);
  backdrop-filter: blur(25px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(25px);
  padding: 0.5rem 0.7rem;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  z-index: 1;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10);
  transition: transform 0.14s ease, box-shadow 0.14s ease, border-color 0.14s ease;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

Visited typography:
```css
.visited-profile-widget-title {
  margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;
  font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  font-weight: 650;
}
.visited-profile-widget-note {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  line-height: 1.45;
}
.visited-profile-widget-block-text {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--text-color);
  margin: 0;
}
```

### Expanded Modal Styles:
```css
.visited-profile-widget-expanded {
  position: relative;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  width: 720px;
  max-width: 92vw;
  max-height: 88vh;
  background-color: var(--bg-elevated);
  border-radius: 20px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--border-light), 0 8px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12), 0 24px 64px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

### Global CSS Variables (index.css):
The project uses CSS custom properties with dark mode support:
- `--bg-glass: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.23)` (light) / `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08)` (dark)
- `--bg-card: #FAFAF8` (light) / `rgb(24, 24, 22)` (dark)
- `--border-light: rgba(151, 151, 151, 0.168)`
- `--font-ui: "Inter", "Nunito", sans-serif`
- Existing font imports: "Lexend Deca", "Inter", "Nunito", "Lora"

### Widget Image Styles:
```css
.profile-widget-image {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 340px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  object-fit: cover;
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
}
.visited-profile-widget-image {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 10px;
  object-fit: cover;
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
}
```

## Requirements
1. Copy the card style from the reference: warm cream background, soft rounded corners, soft shadow
2. Copy the font style: handwritten/casual font for widget content (titles, notes, block text)
3. Apply consistently to BOTH MyProfile widgets AND VisitProfile widgets
4. Also style the expanded widget modal in VisitProfile to match
5. Keep all the existing interactive states (dragging, resizing, editing, active) working - just update the visual base
6. Maintain dark mode support (the warm cream should have a dark equivalent)
7. Don't break the layout/positioning system (absolute positioning, blocks, etc.)

## Design the Plan
Please provide a detailed, step-by-step implementation plan that covers:
1. Which Google Font to import (handwritten style matching the reference)
2. New CSS variables to add to index.css
3. Exact CSS changes for myprofile.css widget classes
4. Exact CSS changes for visitProfile.css widget classes
5. Any changes needed to the expanded modal
6. How to handle dark mode for the warm cream background

Focus on CSS-only changes - no component/JSX modifications should be needed since we're just restyling.

