## Implementation Plan: Restyling Profile Widgets to Warm Handwritten Card Style

### Overview

This plan covers CSS-only changes across 3 files to transform the widget cards from their current glass-morphism style to a warm, hand-crafted card aesthetic with handwritten fonts. No JSX/component changes are required. The existing inline `bg_color` overrides will continue to work because they apply via `style={{backgroundColor: ...}}`, which takes precedence over CSS background -- meaning our CSS background is just the new default.

---

### Step 1: Add Handwritten Font to Google Fonts Import

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\index.css` (line 1)

**Font Choice: "Patrick Hand"**

Patrick Hand is the best match for the reference design. It is a clean, legible handwritten font with a casual-but-readable character. It looks like natural handwriting without being overly decorative, and it works well at small sizes (0.78rem-0.95rem) which is critical since the widget text is compact. "Caveat" is more of a cursive script and harder to read at small sizes. "Comic Neue" is more cartoon-like than handwritten. Patrick Hand strikes the right balance.

**Change:** Modify the existing `@import url(...)` on line 1 to add `family=Patrick+Hand` to the URL query string.

Current URL contains:
```
family=Comfortaa:wght@300..700&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=Lexend+Deca:wght@100..900&family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,500&family=Nunito:ital,wght@0,200..1000;1,200..1000&family=Shadows+Into+Light&family=Sniglet:wght@400;800
```

New URL should add before `&display=swap`:
```
&family=Patrick+Hand
```

So the full new import becomes:
```css
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Comfortaa:wght@300..700&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=Lexend+Deca:wght@100..900&family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,500&family=Nunito:ital,wght@0,200..1000;1,200..1000&family=Patrick+Hand&family=Shadows+Into+Light&family=Sniglet:wght@400;800&display=swap');
```

